Program.Title: Medical Coding-CA
Program.Description: The BCIS department offers a Certificate of Achievement in Medical Coding for those who want to pursue a career as medical coders and/or billers. The medical coder and biller is responsible for reviewing patient health records, assigning appropriate codes to diagnoses and procedures performed by the healthcare provider, and submitting claims for reimbursement and collecting payments. The Bureau of Labor Statistics is predicting that this field is growing due to an aging population requiring more medical services and an increased number of individuals who have access to health insurance because of federal health insurance reform.
